"title": "5727: old age, attitudes to",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5727: old age, attitudes to",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Old age is generally held in honour and the aged in society are to be respected. Because of the wisdom associated with their advancing years elders had an important role of authority and guidance in Israelite society and the NT speaks of the leadership of elders within the church.</p>\n<h2>Old age is to be held in honour</h2>\n<h3>Respect for the aged</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:32\">LEV 19:32</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:5\">1PE 5:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:8\">JOB 29:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:31\">PRO 16:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:29\">PRO 20:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:1\">1TI 5:1</a></p>\n<h3>Respect for parents</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:3\">LEV 19:3</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:22\">PRO 23:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12\">EXO 20:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:17\">EXO 21:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:9\">LEV 20:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:16\">DEU 27:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:17\">PRO 30:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:4\">MAT 15:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:10\">MRK 7:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:1-Eph6:3\">EPH 6:1–6:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:20\">COL 3:20</a></p>\n<h2>Old age is associated with wisdom</h2>\n<h3>Deferring to the wisdom of the aged</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job32:6-Job32:7\">JOB 32:6–32:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:6-1Kgs12:8\">1KI 12:6–12:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:6-2Chr10:8\">2CH 10:6–10:8</a> <em>Rehoboam rejected the advice of elders and rebellion ensued</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job12:12\">JOB 12:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:10\">JOB 15:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:9\">PHM 1:9</a> <em>Paul refers to his age to add authority to his words.</em></p>\n<h3>Learning from the previous generation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:18\">PSA 71:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:8\">JOB 8:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:25-Ps37:26\">PSA 37:25–37:26</a></p>\n<h3>Old age does not necessarily bring superior wisdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:13\">ECC 4:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job32:9\">JOB 32:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:22\">PSA 105:22</a></p>\n<h2>Showing disrespect for the elderly is a sign of evil days</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:5\">ISA 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:50\">DEU 28:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:1\">JOB 30:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:6\">ISA 47:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:12\">LAM 5:12</a></p>\n<h2>The role and status of elders</h2>\n<h3>Elders of non-Israelite nations</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:7\">GEN 50:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:7\">NUM 22:7</a></p>\n<h3>Elders in Israel</h3>\n<p>Israel's elders were probably the heads of families, qualified to lead by virtue of age and experience:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:16-Exod3:18\">EXO 3:16–3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:29-Exod4:31\">EXO 4:29–4:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:7\">EXO 19:7</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:25\">NUM 11:25</a> <em>The number of elders is reduced to 70 who are anointed by the Spirit for leadership alongside Moses.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:11-Deut19:12\">DEU 19:11–19:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:15-Deut22:18\">DEU 22:15–22:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:7\">DEU 25:7</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:3\">2SA 5:3</a> <em>Israel's elders accept David as king</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:57\">MAT 26:57</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:53\">MRK 14:53</a> <em>Jewish elders were among those who tried Jesus Christ. By NT times they had become involved with religious as well as civil affairs and their title related more to their role than to age.</em></p>\n<h3>Elders in the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17\">1TI 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:1-1Tim3:7\">1TI 3:1–3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:5-Titus1:9\">TIT 1:5–1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:14\">JAS 5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:1-1Pet5:2\">1PE 5:1–5:2</a></p>\n<h2>God as the ``Ancient of Days''</h2>\n<h3>God as one ``advanced in years''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:9\">DAN 7:9</a></strong> <em>This description of God as the “Ancient of Days” implies that he possesses the respectability, authority and wisdom to judge that accompanies age. It also points to his eternity.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:13\">DAN 7:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:22\">DAN 7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:14\">REV 1:14</a></p>\n<h3>The eternity of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps9:7\">PSA 9:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps29:10\">PSA 29:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:2\">PSA 90:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:4\">ISA 41:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:6\">ISA 44:6</a></p>",
